<item>
            <title>[DATACMNS-531] Add support for a simplified syntax in request parameters for Sort</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/DATACMNS-531</link>
                <project id="10510" key="DATACMNS">Spring Data Commons</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sorting with Spring Data 1.6 is achieved with request like &lt;tt&gt;?size=100&amp;amp;sort=field,asc&lt;/tt&gt;. Wouldn&apos;t it be much easier &amp;amp; concise if the request is like &lt;tt&gt;?size=100&amp;amp;sort=&amp;#43;field1,&amp;#45;field2&lt;/tt&gt; where &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#43;&lt;/tt&gt; indicates sort ascending and &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&lt;/tt&gt; descending.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="58624">DATACMNS-531</key>
