                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="105638" author="springuser007" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 05:57:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Any comments/thoughts on this request? I feel this is the best &amp;amp; concise representation.&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="105640" author="olivergierke" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 06:07:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;No comments actually. It&apos;s just not very high prio. Sorting basically works and it shouldn&apos;t make too much of a difference to clients to produce either of these formats. Happy to see a pull request though. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you think about submitting one, make sure the APIs and/or implementation for choosing one pattern over the other clearly separate between the two. We&apos;ve had a similar situation (supporting two formats) with a previous style and it added quite a bit of implementation complexity and cognitive load to explain to the users. As we basically have something working I currently don&apos;t see too much priority to add just yet another format.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="105642" author="olivergierke" created="Fri, 11 Jul 2014 06:08:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bumped the priority to avoid implying this is a trivial thing to do (not so much the general implementation part, but also the effects on configuration and user documentation).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
